================================================================================
  UNJYNX Asset Optimization Checklist
  Last Updated: 2026-03-11
================================================================================

TOTAL ASSET BUDGET: < 2 MB
This checklist covers every asset category that ends up in the APK.
Follow it before every release build.

================================================================================
  1. IMAGES
================================================================================

FORMAT RULES:
  [x] Icons and illustrations  -> SVG (vector, scales to any DPI, tiny)
  [x] Photographs / complex    -> WebP (lossy, quality 75-85)
  [x] No PNG larger than 50 KB -> convert to WebP or SVG
  [x] No JPEG in assets        -> always WebP (30-50% smaller)
  [x] No BMP or TIFF ever

SIZE LIMITS:
  [x] Individual image < 100 KB
  [x] Total images budget < 500 KB
  [x] Use flutter_svg for SVG rendering (no rasterization at build time)

RESOLUTION RULES:
  [x] Provide only 1x assets; let Flutter scale up
      (mdpi is enough -- Flutter handles density scaling)
  [x] For raster images that must be crisp: provide 2x and 3x ONLY if
      the visual quality difference is obvious at those densities
  [x] Never include 4x assets (no devices need them)

TOOLS:
  - squoosh.app      -- WebP conversion with quality slider
  - svgo             -- Optimize SVGs (remove editor metadata)
  - tinypng.com      -- Lossless PNG compression

================================================================================
  2. FONTS
================================================================================

RULES:
  [x] Use google_fonts package for runtime font downloading
      -> Fonts are cached after first download
      -> Zero bytes in APK for Google Fonts
  [x] Do NOT bundle .ttf/.otf in assets/ for Google Fonts families
  [x] If a custom (non-Google) font is required:
      - Subset to only used characters (pyftsubset)
      - Use .woff2 if possible, otherwise .otf
      - Max 100 KB per font weight
      - Max 2 weights per family (Regular + Bold)
  [x] Current fonts (Outfit, DM Sans, Bebas Neue, Playfair Display):
      All available via google_fonts -- do NOT bundle manually

TOOL:
  - pyftsubset (from fonttools):
    pyftsubset Font.ttf --unicodes="U+0000-00FF,U+0131,U+0152-0153" \
      --layout-features='*' --flavor=woff2 --output-file=Font.woff2

================================================================================
  3. LOTTIE ANIMATIONS
================================================================================

RULES:
  [x] Each .json Lottie file < 100 KB
  [x] Total Lottie budget < 300 KB
  [x] Strip unused layers in After Effects before export
  [x] Reduce keyframes (every 2nd frame is usually enough)
  [x] Use shape layers, avoid rasterized images in Lottie
  [x] If a Lottie > 100 KB, consider:
      - Simplifying the animation
      - Converting to Rive (.riv) which is more compact
      - Using Flutter's built-in animation APIs instead
  [x] Compress with lottie-minify or manually strip metadata

TOOL:
  - lottiefiles.com/tools/lottie-to-dotlottie (40-70% smaller)
  - Manual: remove "nm" (name) fields from JSON

================================================================================
  4. SOUNDS / AUDIO
================================================================================

RULES:
  [x] Format: OGG Vorbis (.ogg) -- best compression-to-quality ratio
  [x] Channels: Mono (single channel) -- halves file size vs stereo
  [x] Bitrate: 64 kbps (sufficient for UI sounds and notification tones)
  [x] Each sound file < 15 KB
  [x] Total audio budget < 200 KB
  [x] For ambient sounds (Pomodoro): stream from network or local cache,
      do NOT bundle in APK
  [x] No .mp3 (larger), no .wav (uncompressed), no .m4a in assets

TOOL:
  - ffmpeg -i input.wav -ac 1 -b:a 64k -vn output.ogg
  - Audacity: Export as OGG, Quality 3 (64 kbps), Mono

================================================================================
  5. MATERIAL ICONS & TREE SHAKING
================================================================================

RULES:
  [x] Always build with --tree-shake-icons flag
  [x] This removes unused Material and Cupertino icon glyphs
  [x] MaterialIcons-Regular.otf drops from ~1.6 MB to typically < 50 KB
  [x] Verify: pubspec.yaml has `uses-material-design: true`
      (required for tree shaking to work)
  [x] If using custom icon fonts (e.g., from icomoon), subset them to
      only the glyphs you actually use

HOW TO VERIFY:
  flutter build apk --release --tree-shake-icons
  # Check: build output should say "Font asset 'MaterialIcons-Regular.otf'
  # was tree-shaken, reducing from XXXX to YYYY"

================================================================================
  6. DART AOT CODE SIZE
================================================================================

RULES:
  [x] Use --obfuscate to minify Dart symbols (5-15% smaller AOT)
  [x] Use deferred loading for feature packages not needed at startup:
      - feature_gamification  (deferred)
      - feature_billing       (deferred)
      - feature_widgets       (deferred)
      - feature_team          (deferred)
      - feature_import_export (deferred)
  [x] Avoid importing entire packages when only one class is needed
  [x] Run: bash scripts/deferred-imports-check.sh
  [x] Use --split-debug-info to separate debug symbols from release binary

================================================================================
  7. NATIVE LIBRARIES
================================================================================

RULES:
  [x] Use --split-per-abi to avoid bundling all architectures in one APK
  [x] For Play Store: use AAB (App Bundle) -- Google handles ABI splitting
  [x] Review native dependencies:
      - awesome_notifications: has native code (~1-2 MB per ABI)
      - drift/sqlite3: has native sqlite (~500 KB per ABI)
      - Each native plugin adds per-ABI overhead
  [x] If APK exceeds 15 MB, audit: flutter build apk --analyze-size

================================================================================
  8. PROGUARD / R8 (Android)
================================================================================

RULES:
  [x] R8 is enabled by default in release builds (via Gradle)
  [x] If you add custom ProGuard rules, put them in:
      apps/mobile/android/app/proguard-rules.pro
  [x] Verify no "Missing class" warnings in release build
  [x] Keep rules for reflection-heavy libraries (if any)

================================================================================
  9. VERIFICATION COMMANDS
================================================================================

# Full size analysis (builds + parses report)
bash scripts/apk-size-analysis.sh

# Skip build, just analyze existing report
bash scripts/apk-size-analysis.sh --skip-build

# Build release APKs (split per ABI)
bash scripts/build-release.sh apk

# Build release AAB (Play Store)
bash scripts/build-release.sh aab

# Check deferred imports
bash scripts/deferred-imports-check.sh

# Interactive size explorer (opens DevTools)
flutter pub global run devtools --appSizeBase=<path-to-json>

# Quick APK contents listing (requires Android SDK build-tools)
# Shows what's inside the APK and how much space each entry takes
unzip -l build/app/outputs/flutter-apk/app-arm64-v8a-release.apk | sort -nrk1 | head -20

================================================================================
  10. SIZE TARGETS
================================================================================

  Platform      Format          Target     Hard Limit
  ----------    -----------     -------    ----------
  arm64         APK             < 15 MB    20 MB
  armeabi-v7a   APK             < 12 MB    18 MB
  universal     APK             < 20 MB    30 MB
  Play Store    AAB             < 15 MB    150 MB (Play limit)

  Category          Budget
  --------          ------
  Dart AOT          < 8 MB
  Native libs       < 4 MB (per ABI)
  Assets (total)    < 2 MB
  - Images          < 500 KB
  - Fonts           < 0 KB (use google_fonts)
  - Lottie          < 300 KB
  - Audio           < 200 KB
  - Other           < 200 KB
  Resources (res/)  < 500 KB
  DEX               < 1 MB

================================================================================
  11. PRE-RELEASE CHECKLIST
================================================================================

  [ ] Run `bash scripts/deferred-imports-check.sh` -- 0 violations
  [ ] Run `bash scripts/apk-size-analysis.sh` -- all under budget
  [ ] No PNG > 50 KB in assets
  [ ] No bundled Google Fonts (using google_fonts package)
  [ ] No .mp3 or .wav in assets (OGG only)
  [ ] No Lottie > 100 KB
  [ ] --tree-shake-icons confirmed in build command
  [ ] --obfuscate confirmed in build command
  [ ] --split-debug-info confirmed in build command
  [ ] Debug symbols uploaded to Sentry
  [ ] AAB uploaded to Play Console (internal track first)
  [ ] Test install on a real arm64 device

================================================================================
